Durban – A group of armed men robbed a clothing store at Cornubia Mall today.Cornubia Mall general manager Lara Gracie confirmed that the robbery occurred at approximately 11am.“Armed suspects robbed a clothing store of merchandise to an undisclosed value at Cornubia Mall,” said Gracie.She said SAPS, private security armed response and local law enforcement were notified.“There were no injuries reported. Shopper safety remains a priority for the management of Cornubia Mall and we are awaiting a completed incident report,” said Gracie.MORE ON THISMourners robbed of jewellery, cellphone in church parking lot in Overport, DurbanAnother Gauteng vaccination team robbed of vaccination equipment and cellphonesProvincial police spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said the complainant alleged that this morning at 11am, he was performing his duties with his colleagues in a clothing store at a shopping centre in Verulam when they were accosted by a group of armed men.“At gunpoint the suspects removed clothes, cellphones and fled the scene in their getaway vehicle,” said Mbele.The Mercury